    "Name": "Saracen HCV",
    "Details": "Replacing the LRM-10 with an MRM-20 is one of the few official variants of the Saracen. This version is mostly employed by the DCMS. It also removes the SRM-2 launchers and replaces them with a single Streak SRM-2 launcher. The Saracen is a well-designed hovercraft: it is fast and decently armored. It has endeared itself to its crews due to its reliability and ruggedness and forms the backbone of many striker units. The Saracen was developed towards the end of the Third Succession War by Scarborough Limited. Shortly afterward Scarborough created two other vehicles based on the Saracen, the Scimitar and the Saladin.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>ICE: Air breathing Combustion Engine. This unit can not deploy in thin atmosphere.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 8/12 hexes / 240/360 meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Ferro-Fibrous\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       150     20\n<b>Left</b>         110     20\n<b>Right</b>       110     20\n<b>Rear</b>        120     20\n<b>Turret</b>      130     20\n\n<b>Total</b>      620    100</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Rugged</color>",
